WEBVTT

00:03.670 --> 00:06.330
Meredith: For surgeons,
every day is game day.

00:06.330 --> 00:08.000
[ Izzy Bizu's
"Adam & Eve" plays ]

00:08.000 --> 00:12.460
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

00:12.460 --> 00:14.250
[ Groans ]

00:14.250 --> 00:15.880
♪ Yeah, yeah ♪
[ Sighs ]

00:15.880 --> 00:16.920
♪ Deeper I struggle,
deeper I get ♪

00:16.920 --> 00:17.960
I'm gonna have to
sneak you out.

00:17.960 --> 00:18.960
[ Groans ]
[ Laughs ]

00:18.960 --> 00:20.830
I feel so dirty.

00:20.830 --> 00:22.420
Dirty, dirty secret.

00:22.420 --> 00:23.920
I'm just not ready
for my nieces and nephew

00:23.920 --> 00:25.120
to see you.

00:25.120 --> 00:26.880
You're married,
aren't you?

00:26.880 --> 00:28.670
No single woman
lives in a house like this.

00:28.670 --> 00:30.080
What? No!

00:30.080 --> 00:32.330
You're kidding,
r--

00:32.330 --> 00:33.670
♪ Damn, you look so sweet ♪
Oh, you are kidding.

00:33.670 --> 00:36.120
You got jokes.
Yeah, from time to time.

00:36.120 --> 00:37.580
We've trained. We've practiced.
♪ I'm gonna get it,
get it ♪

00:37.580 --> 00:38.710
[ Laughs ]
[ Elevator bell dings ]

00:38.710 --> 00:39.790
We know the rules.

00:39.790 --> 00:43.380
No, no! 18 max.

00:43.380 --> 00:46.380
♪ You hold me ransom
every time ♪

00:46.380 --> 00:50.460
Okay, I really miss sex,
and this is not helping.

00:50.460 --> 00:52.040
[ Sighs ]

00:52.040 --> 00:53.750
Are you having sex?

00:53.750 --> 00:55.830
Mm, on occasion.

00:55.830 --> 00:57.670
Are you thinking about it
all the time?

00:57.670 --> 00:59.250
I'm thinking about it
right now.

00:59.250 --> 01:01.040
I'm almost positive
this constitutes

01:01.040 --> 01:03.920
a hostile
work environment.

01:03.920 --> 01:05.920
Note taken.
[ Elevator bell dings ]

01:05.920 --> 01:07.580
♪ Stranger ♪

01:07.580 --> 01:09.040
Well, hang in there.

01:09.040 --> 01:10.420
[ Chuckles ]
♪ Stranger ♪

01:10.420 --> 01:13.080
♪ Stranger ♪

01:13.080 --> 01:15.710
[ Telephone rings ]

01:15.710 --> 01:17.420
Are you thinking about
sex all the time

01:17.420 --> 01:18.920
with the noises
through the wall?

01:18.920 --> 01:20.830
I am not that loud.

01:20.830 --> 01:22.500
The walls are thin.

01:22.500 --> 01:25.080
I miss sex.
Don't you?

01:25.080 --> 01:27.210
My sex drive has become
my work drive.

01:27.210 --> 01:30.080
Plus, I got this really
excellent back massager.

01:30.080 --> 01:31.920
Clive is nice.
You know?

01:31.920 --> 01:33.290
Like, it's more than sex.

01:33.290 --> 01:34.670
I think
I really like him.

01:34.670 --> 01:35.790
I'm seeing him
again tonight.

01:35.790 --> 01:37.000
You're already at
two nights in a row,

01:37.000 --> 01:38.040
and you think
you like him?

01:38.040 --> 01:39.500
Well, my mom
was the one

01:39.500 --> 01:41.330
who always told me whether
a guy was a keeper or...

01:41.330 --> 01:42.420
A serial killer.

01:42.420 --> 01:44.380
He's not a serial killer.
He's too nice.

01:44.380 --> 01:45.710
You know who says that?

01:45.710 --> 01:47.330
Neighbors
of serial killers.

01:47.330 --> 01:49.210
We should meet him.

01:49.210 --> 01:51.210
Judging boyfriends
is the number-one perk

01:51.210 --> 01:52.500
of having sisters
with no sex lives.

01:52.500 --> 01:53.960
Tonight?

01:53.960 --> 01:56.750
Sure. My thing with
Dr. Cerone doesn't go well,

01:56.750 --> 01:58.170
I may just stay home

01:58.170 --> 02:00.420
and get drunk
with my back massager.

02:00.420 --> 02:02.620
I like this idea
of a sister panel.

02:02.620 --> 02:03.710
So, what?
Dinner?

02:03.710 --> 02:06.120
No, more casual.

02:06.120 --> 02:08.000
Game night.
Game night?

02:08.000 --> 02:09.250
And he'll have no idea
that the real game

02:09.250 --> 02:10.880
is us judging him.

02:10.880 --> 02:12.620
I'll spread the word.

02:12.620 --> 02:15.710
[ Indistinct conversations ]

02:15.710 --> 02:19.000
Game night
at Grey's place. Sweet.

02:19.000 --> 02:21.040
Pretty sure
we weren't invited.

02:21.040 --> 02:23.080
[ Coughing ]

02:23.080 --> 02:24.580
Casey:
She's been like this a while.

02:24.580 --> 02:27.920
Uh, I had some bad chicken salad
from the cafeteria.

02:27.920 --> 02:29.960
No, you didn't.
Snitch.

02:29.960 --> 02:32.330
I know you don't want it, but we
need to put in an NG tube.

02:32.330 --> 02:33.380
You need the nutrients.

02:33.380 --> 02:35.960
No, please.
I-I hate that thing.

02:35.960 --> 02:38.460
It hurts so bad,
and I can't sing.

02:38.460 --> 02:39.750
[ Retches ]

02:39.750 --> 02:42.830
I'm sorry, but the anti-nausea
meds aren't working.

02:42.830 --> 02:44.460
That's the only option.

02:44.460 --> 02:46.380
[ Sighs ]

02:46.380 --> 02:48.960
I need you to get me
some weed.
Excuse me?

02:48.960 --> 02:50.380
I think she means
marijuana.

02:50.380 --> 02:52.500
Yeah, I know what she meant,
and the answer is no.

02:52.500 --> 02:55.290
But it's legal in Washington.
When you're 18.

02:55.290 --> 02:57.250
[ Scoffs ] I'm talking about
medical marijuana.

02:57.250 --> 02:58.460
You've been Googling.

02:58.460 --> 03:00.580
There's an oil.
It won't get me high.

03:00.580 --> 03:02.920
All I need is authorization
from the hospital

03:02.920 --> 03:05.210
and my primary physician.

03:05.210 --> 03:06.580
It eases the pain,
nausea.

03:06.580 --> 03:09.000
It's been shown to
help patients on chemo.

03:09.000 --> 03:10.580
With PTSD.

03:10.580 --> 03:13.080
Look, it's not regulated
or approved by the FDA.

03:13.080 --> 03:15.500
Was this your idea?
No, it was my grandma's.

03:15.500 --> 03:19.750
[ Retches ]

03:19.750 --> 03:20.880
[ Breathing deeply ]

03:20.880 --> 03:24.540
[ Mouse squeaking ]

03:24.540 --> 03:25.620
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

03:25.620 --> 03:27.500
Is he still alive?
He's not just alive.

03:27.500 --> 03:29.290
He's freaking celebrating
that he's alive!

03:29.290 --> 03:31.120
Don't anthropomorphize
the mouse.

03:31.120 --> 03:33.210
Jo: Okay, well, I am celebrating
that he is alive.

03:33.210 --> 03:34.080
He should've been dead
three days ago.

03:34.080 --> 03:35.540
He has no liver!

03:35.540 --> 03:37.960
Why are you screaming at me?
B-Because this is big.

03:37.960 --> 03:39.580
I mean, we injected him
with hepatocytes.

03:39.580 --> 03:41.460
He grew mini livers,
and they're working,

03:41.460 --> 03:43.120
and you are being
way too calm.

03:43.120 --> 03:45.710
Because it's only a big deal
if Cerone gives us the patent.

03:45.710 --> 03:47.420
And we can't
show him the mouse.

03:47.420 --> 03:50.080
Because we used his polymer
without his permission?

03:50.080 --> 03:52.380
Yeah, and if he sees
how well this is working,

03:52.380 --> 03:54.540
he'll drive the price up
into the millions.

03:54.540 --> 03:57.330
Okay, she is really peeing
on my parade today.

03:57.330 --> 03:59.170
Cerone is dead.

03:59.170 --> 04:00.330
And the parade
is canceled.

04:00.330 --> 04:01.620
He's dead?
Yeah.

04:01.620 --> 04:03.080
He, uh, died last week.

04:03.080 --> 04:05.170
That's why
they've been stalling.

04:05.170 --> 04:06.540
So who's in charge
of the patent?

04:06.540 --> 04:09.080
His daughter. That's who
you're meeting with today.

04:09.080 --> 04:10.290
You couldn't have
led with that, Hellmouth?

04:10.290 --> 04:11.460
What do we know
about the daughter?

04:11.460 --> 04:13.290
Nothing. I can't find
anything online,

04:13.290 --> 04:14.620
but you look amazing
in that dress.

04:16.040 --> 04:17.670
Excuse me?

04:17.670 --> 04:21.790
Nothing.
Sorry. Nothing.

04:21.790 --> 04:23.420
Will this affect my hearing?
Nope.

04:23.420 --> 04:24.750
There's just
a collection of blood

04:24.750 --> 04:28.080
in your outer ear
that needs draining.

04:28.080 --> 04:29.330
I've never heard
of coed rugby.

04:29.330 --> 04:30.790
How long
have you been playing?

04:30.790 --> 04:33.080
Sarah doesn't play.
She's the manager.

04:33.080 --> 04:34.080
Yeah, you're glad
I don't.

04:34.080 --> 04:35.670
I'd crush you, Duran.
Ha!

04:35.670 --> 04:37.540
Hey, Bachmann.

04:37.540 --> 04:40.250
Oh, hey, no throwing
that ball in here, okay?

04:40.250 --> 04:42.540
I, uh, have this heart thing
since I was a kid.

04:42.540 --> 04:45.120
So, I was on the sidelines
when a ruck got out of control.

04:45.120 --> 04:46.420
I don't need surgery,
do I?

04:46.420 --> 04:48.330
Nope, I'm gonna do this
right here.

04:48.330 --> 04:50.120
I just gave you a field block
to numb your ear.

04:50.120 --> 04:51.120
You shouldn't
feel a thing.

04:51.120 --> 04:53.210
Aaah!

04:53.210 --> 04:54.750
You know,
I need another hand here.

04:54.750 --> 04:57.040
-Uh, DeLuca.
-Coming.

04:57.040 --> 04:58.960
Do you know,
are interns invited to

04:58.960 --> 05:01.290
this game thing tonight at --
at Dr. Pierce's?

05:01.290 --> 05:03.210
Games?
I love games.

05:03.210 --> 05:05.960
Hey, stop throwing
the ball in my ER!

05:05.960 --> 05:07.210
Here's your ball,
Bachmann.

05:07.210 --> 05:08.710
Ohh!

05:08.710 --> 05:10.670
♪♪

05:10.670 --> 05:11.880
Heads!

05:11.880 --> 05:16.000
Aah!

05:16.000 --> 05:17.000
[ Gasping ]
Oh, God.

05:17.000 --> 05:18.620
What happened?
Oh, God.

05:18.620 --> 05:19.880
What is it?
Okay, I need
more four-by-fours.

05:19.880 --> 05:21.960
I got them.

05:21.960 --> 05:23.170
Wah!

05:23.170 --> 05:24.330
-Whoa!
-Hey!

05:24.330 --> 05:26.080
[ All murmuring ]

05:26.080 --> 05:27.080
Aaah!

05:27.080 --> 05:29.830
Okay, it's okay.
It's okay.

05:29.830 --> 05:32.330
Okay.
You okay, DeLuca?

05:32.330 --> 05:34.580
Yep.
I'm just gonna...

05:34.580 --> 05:35.920
No.

05:35.920 --> 05:37.250
[ Groans ]

05:52.920 --> 05:54.120
[ Sighs ] Wait.
I-I slipped on someone's ear?

05:54.120 --> 05:56.330
Was it attached
to their head?

05:56.330 --> 05:57.750
Not at the time.

05:57.750 --> 06:01.210
Okay, no intracranial bleeding
or swelling.
[ Sighs ]

06:01.210 --> 06:03.250
Congratulations.
It's a grade-3 concussion.

06:03.250 --> 06:04.670
What's the treatment?

06:04.670 --> 06:09.540
Uh...rest, minimal stimuli,
dim lights, no screens.

06:09.540 --> 06:11.880
Good.
Cognitive skills still intact.

06:11.880 --> 06:14.540
You are staying in
a patient room tonight.

06:14.540 --> 06:18.420
[ Sighs ]
Ugh.

06:18.420 --> 06:21.830
Oh, hey,
did Sam see me fall?

06:21.830 --> 06:24.210
Dr. Bello --
Did Sam Bello see me fall?

06:26.420 --> 06:29.710
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
on P.A. ]

06:29.710 --> 06:31.040
I have to have surgery?
You have to put me out?

06:31.040 --> 06:32.170
[ Indistinct conversations ]

06:32.170 --> 06:34.500
For me to reattach
the ear, yes.

06:34.500 --> 06:37.080
Can it even be reattached?
That guy smooshed it.

06:37.080 --> 06:39.290
That's fine.
Most ears are smooshed, anyway.

06:39.290 --> 06:41.210
And once it's healed up,
you'll barely notice it.

06:41.210 --> 06:43.000
[ Sighs ]
What happened here?

06:43.000 --> 06:44.000
Hey.
Hi.

06:44.000 --> 06:45.170
Um, long story.

06:45.170 --> 06:47.170
Sarah,
this is Dr. Pierce.

06:47.170 --> 06:48.750
She is our chief of cardio.

06:48.750 --> 06:51.580
Sarah tells me she has
ventricular septal defect, so...

06:51.580 --> 06:53.920
Little hole in your heart.
Since I was a kid.

06:53.920 --> 06:56.120
And she's a little worried
about the anesthesia.

06:56.120 --> 06:58.250
More worried
about calling my dad.

06:58.250 --> 06:59.750
He's gonna be so pissed.

06:59.750 --> 07:02.290
Well, let's take a look.

07:02.290 --> 07:03.500
Um, okay.

07:03.500 --> 07:04.790
I will come check on you
before the surgery, okay?

07:04.790 --> 07:06.540
Thanks.

07:06.540 --> 07:10.830
[ Monitor beeping ]

07:10.830 --> 07:12.830
Do you two have a thing?

07:12.830 --> 07:14.670
He's so nice.

07:14.670 --> 07:16.420
A thing? Us?

07:16.420 --> 07:18.620
I-I just figured maybe
because, you know,

07:18.620 --> 07:20.210
there were
a lot of vibes.

07:20.210 --> 07:21.580
No, I have a...

07:21.580 --> 07:24.080
You have a boyfriend
that's better than that?

07:24.080 --> 07:26.500
I would like to see him,
please.

07:26.500 --> 07:28.420
Let's go take a look
at your heart.

07:28.420 --> 07:29.790
♪♪

07:29.790 --> 07:31.540
I don't understand
why you're upset.

07:31.540 --> 07:33.040
Because this is
my OB department,

07:33.040 --> 07:35.170
which means you work
for me and...
Ooh, Dr. Lackman.

07:35.170 --> 07:37.670
You paged me?
Yeah. Yes. Yes.

07:37.670 --> 07:40.710
Dr. DeLuca is asking
for all of my OB records.

07:40.710 --> 07:43.420
She says you're launching
some kind of investigation.

07:43.420 --> 07:45.500
Oh, no, no, not --
not an investigation -- a study.

07:45.500 --> 07:46.620
It's a study.
That's what I said.

07:46.620 --> 07:48.000
Well, I know,
but you also called

07:48.000 --> 07:50.830
a seat belt a "strap-on," so,
you know, sometimes, uh...

07:50.830 --> 07:51.960
Um, it's a study.

07:51.960 --> 07:53.750
It's a maternal
mortality study

07:53.750 --> 07:55.710
on cases in the U.S. versus
other developed countries.

07:55.710 --> 07:56.960
Oh.
Yeah.

07:56.960 --> 07:58.540
It's for the medical
innovation contest.

07:58.540 --> 07:59.580
Ah.

07:59.580 --> 08:01.290
Hey, by the way,
Sofia keeps asking

08:01.290 --> 08:03.080
if she can have
a playdate with Lindsay.

08:03.080 --> 08:05.120
Oh, seems like they were just
in the daycare together.

08:05.120 --> 08:06.880
I know.
It goes too fast.

08:06.880 --> 08:09.250
Here's my log-in and password.
Use what you need.

08:09.250 --> 08:11.330
Mm.
And call me.
Let's set up a playdate.

08:11.330 --> 08:14.000
Yeah. Definitely.
Okay.

08:14.000 --> 08:16.040
[ Telephone ringing ]

08:16.040 --> 08:17.330
You want it?
[ Laughs ]

08:17.330 --> 08:18.500
You want it?
Come on.

08:18.500 --> 08:19.790
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
on P.A. ]

08:19.790 --> 08:21.620
[ Sighs ] Okay.
Let's take a look at that leg.

08:21.620 --> 08:23.420
Uh, no. No way.

08:23.420 --> 08:25.580
You're the one that chopped
that girl's ear off.

08:25.580 --> 08:27.710
Oh, you mean Sarah,
the girl who lost her ear

08:27.710 --> 08:29.710
because you couldn't follow
a simple direction?

08:29.710 --> 08:31.420
I want someone else,
a different doctor.

08:31.420 --> 08:34.540
Fine.

08:34.540 --> 08:36.830
[ Laughs ] Schmitt!

08:36.830 --> 08:38.000
There's your someone else.

08:38.000 --> 08:40.290
Uh, pass. I'd like a doctor
who's older than me.

08:40.290 --> 08:42.120
Well, we're a little short
on doctors today

08:42.120 --> 08:43.750
'cause someone threw
a ball.

08:43.750 --> 08:46.120
So we're just gonna call this
a teaching moment.

08:46.120 --> 08:47.880
For...me or him?

08:47.880 --> 08:49.120
Ugh! Does it matter?

08:49.120 --> 08:50.500
All right.

08:50.500 --> 08:52.380
Uh, now I need you
to get a solid base

08:52.380 --> 08:54.040
before you reduce
that fracture.

08:54.040 --> 08:55.880
I already lost an ear.
Hate to lose a foot.

08:55.880 --> 08:57.000
W-What?

08:57.000 --> 08:58.500
Hold up, Schmitt.

08:58.500 --> 09:02.830
Kepner, can I, uh,
talk to you for a second?

09:02.830 --> 09:06.120
Um, so, I'm gonna take over, and
you can head home for the day.

09:06.120 --> 09:08.080
What?
Chief's orders.

09:08.080 --> 09:09.460
She's talking to legal,

09:09.460 --> 09:11.210
and they said
that you should stand down.

09:11.210 --> 09:12.500
Wait. S-- I'm --
[ Chuckles ]

09:12.500 --> 09:14.120
I'm getting suspended?
Why?

09:14.120 --> 09:16.170
Well, you cut a girl's ear off,
for starters.

09:16.170 --> 09:17.170
It's only for the day.

09:17.170 --> 09:18.960
Yeah, because
a kid was throwing a ball

09:18.960 --> 09:20.330
after I repeatedly told him
to stop.

09:20.330 --> 09:21.500
Yes,
everybody knows that,

09:21.500 --> 09:22.920
and the security video
will affirm that.

09:22.920 --> 09:24.210
Okay,
what's the problem, then?

09:24.210 --> 09:26.000
The problem is
I heard it from Bailey,

09:26.000 --> 09:28.290
she heard it from Webber,
and you never reported it?
[ Sighs ]

09:28.290 --> 09:29.830
An accident in your ER...
I --

09:29.830 --> 09:31.710
...resulting
in a mangled patient

09:31.710 --> 09:34.380
and an injured surgeon
could mean major lawsuits.

09:34.380 --> 09:35.380
And there's
no incident report?

09:35.380 --> 09:36.960
No, I was gonna do it later.
You don't mention it to me?

09:36.960 --> 09:38.290
I was working. I --
What is going on, Kepner?

09:38.290 --> 09:39.380
You know,
wh-what's going on

09:39.380 --> 09:41.210
is that somebody
broke the rules

09:41.210 --> 09:42.620
and somebody else
is getting punished for it.

09:42.620 --> 09:45.120
That's what's going on.

09:45.120 --> 09:49.040
[ Indistinct conversations ]

09:49.040 --> 09:51.040
[ Pulsing ]
Okay, see that color there?

09:51.040 --> 09:53.330
That's where your blood
is flowing through your VSD.

09:53.330 --> 09:54.960
Still there.

09:54.960 --> 09:56.920
They found it
when I was 8.
[ Clicks, pulsing stops ]

09:56.920 --> 09:58.500
But they said
having a big surgery

09:58.500 --> 10:00.540
would be riskier
than just keeping it.

10:00.540 --> 10:02.080
Well,
it was back then.

10:02.080 --> 10:03.960
Now I could use
a catheter

10:03.960 --> 10:05.620
to place a patch
on the hole.

10:05.620 --> 10:08.830
It's way less invasive,
which means way less risky.

10:08.830 --> 10:10.380
Wait. What?

10:10.380 --> 10:12.000
Just like that?
No open-heart surgery?

10:12.000 --> 10:14.380
Nope.

10:14.380 --> 10:16.250
Then my dad
would let me play rugby?

10:16.250 --> 10:19.000
Well, is your dad
anti-rugby?

10:19.000 --> 10:20.830
He's anti-me dying.

10:20.830 --> 10:24.000
He made me quit because of my
heart, so I'm team manager.

10:24.000 --> 10:25.580
But, I mean,
after this,

10:25.580 --> 10:27.670
I could totally
get off the sidelines.

10:27.670 --> 10:29.080
Could you fix it
while you fix my ear?

10:29.080 --> 10:31.040
No, it would have to be
two separate surgeries --

10:31.040 --> 10:33.880
your ear first,
and then your heart.

10:33.880 --> 10:35.290
But I will assist Dr. Avery

10:35.290 --> 10:37.540
with the vascular reconnections
on your ear,

10:37.540 --> 10:40.000
and I can monitor your heart
while I'm there.

10:40.000 --> 10:40.880
[ Bed rail clicking ]

10:40.880 --> 10:41.960
Hmm.

10:41.960 --> 10:43.420
What?

10:43.420 --> 10:45.960
Even when you say his name,
there's vibes.

10:45.960 --> 10:47.040
Stop it.

10:47.040 --> 10:49.080
[ Laughs ]
Please.

10:49.080 --> 10:52.670
[ Indistinct conversations ]

10:52.670 --> 10:54.250
You got a minute?

10:54.250 --> 10:55.960
Ha, do I look like
I have a minute?

10:55.960 --> 10:57.460
You never look like
you have a minute.

10:57.460 --> 10:59.460
Then read my face, and I'll come
find you when I'm done here.

10:59.460 --> 11:01.250
[ Sighs ] I want to give
my 12-year-old patient

11:01.250 --> 11:03.540
authorization
for medical marijuana.

11:03.540 --> 11:07.790
♪♪

11:07.790 --> 11:09.710
Karev, have you met
the Grey Sloan Legal Team?

11:09.710 --> 11:14.540
♪♪

11:14.540 --> 11:15.880
Meredith: So, there's
nothing else online

11:15.880 --> 11:16.750
about Cerone's daughter?

11:16.750 --> 11:18.420
No, she's an only child.

11:18.420 --> 11:19.710
She has an MD after her name.
That's it.

11:19.710 --> 11:21.000
Okay.

11:21.000 --> 11:22.210
So we smile...
Mm.

11:22.210 --> 11:23.670
...uh, act polite,
Mm.

11:23.670 --> 11:27.120
...kill her with kindness,
and we do not mention the mouse.

11:27.120 --> 11:29.250
Do we really have enough
for the presentation without it?

11:29.250 --> 11:31.670
Well, the presentation with it
is definitely too much.

11:31.670 --> 11:32.790
Marie: Meredith?

11:32.790 --> 11:34.920
♪♪

11:34.920 --> 11:39.210
Look at you
all grown up.

11:39.210 --> 11:40.830
Auntie Marie?!

11:40.830 --> 11:42.420
"Mer-Mer"!

11:42.420 --> 11:44.040
[ Both laugh ]

11:44.040 --> 11:45.040
Twist.

11:45.040 --> 11:46.710
♪♪

11:53.790 --> 11:55.040
I was so sorry
to hear about your father.

11:55.040 --> 11:57.210
Oh, thank you.
He was sick for a long time.

11:57.210 --> 11:58.790
It was time.

11:58.790 --> 12:00.380
-And he was ready.
-Hmm.

12:00.380 --> 12:05.080
Ah, you look just the same
but prettier.

12:05.080 --> 12:07.250
And the last time
I saw you was...

12:07.250 --> 12:09.250
8th birthday party.
Oh, my goodness.

12:09.250 --> 12:10.620
The balloons?
The balloons!

12:10.620 --> 12:12.250
[ Laughs ]

12:12.250 --> 12:14.040
She filled
the entire bedroom,

12:14.040 --> 12:15.710
floor to ceiling,
with balloons.

12:15.710 --> 12:17.620
It was...insane.

12:17.620 --> 12:19.670
[ Chuckles ] You were
a disembodied giggle.

12:19.670 --> 12:20.750
[ Both laugh ]

12:20.750 --> 12:22.920
Are you really her...

12:22.920 --> 12:23.790
Oh, no, I'm sorry.

12:23.790 --> 12:25.170
This is Dr. Jo Wilson.

12:25.170 --> 12:26.920
She's my partner
on the project.

12:26.920 --> 12:27.920
This is Marie Cerone.

12:27.920 --> 12:29.540
Hi. So,
are you really her aunt?

12:29.540 --> 12:31.460
N-Not by blood.
[ Chuckles ]

12:31.460 --> 12:34.040
Her mother and I were friends,
best friends.

12:34.040 --> 12:35.620
I watched Meredith grow up.

12:35.620 --> 12:38.540
And then you just sort of
disappeared after...

12:38.540 --> 12:40.080
What -- What --
What happened?

12:40.080 --> 12:41.880
Ugh. Your mother
didn't tell you?

12:41.880 --> 12:43.330
I had to go back to Spain.

12:43.330 --> 12:45.330
My father wanted me
to run the business.

12:45.330 --> 12:47.120
Oh.
Ah!

12:47.120 --> 12:49.080
I just want to squeeze you,
my Mer-Mer!

12:49.080 --> 12:50.210
Mer-Mer?
[ Laughs ]

12:50.210 --> 12:51.790
You don't go
by that anymore?

12:51.790 --> 12:54.710
-Unh.
-Ah!

12:54.710 --> 12:58.210
I really wanted to get in touch
when I heard about Ellis.

12:58.210 --> 13:01.540
I wanted to, but...

13:01.540 --> 13:02.620
[ Whispering ]
It's okay.

13:02.620 --> 13:05.790
I have watched you
all these years.

13:05.790 --> 13:08.250
She would've been proud
of you, Meredith.

13:08.250 --> 13:10.040
She would've been
very proud.

13:10.040 --> 13:14.080
♪♪

13:14.080 --> 13:15.790
[ Indistinct conversations ]

13:15.790 --> 13:17.920
Uh, took a spill
in the kitchen.

13:17.920 --> 13:20.330
Aw. Okay.
Ma'am, let's take a look.
Luke: Someone
had to secure the ball,

13:20.330 --> 13:22.080
and it obviously
wasn't you.
I'm gonna shine
a bright light into your eye.

13:22.080 --> 13:23.080
Oh! You think
you're so hard.

13:23.080 --> 13:24.420
I've been carrying us
all year!

13:24.420 --> 13:25.920
Why don't you come over here
and say that to my face?

13:25.920 --> 13:27.380
Oh, man, you are so lucky
I'm on the bed right now.

13:27.380 --> 13:28.620
I'll be right back.

13:28.620 --> 13:29.670
Luke: If you hadn't
tackled me from behind,

13:29.670 --> 13:30.920
I'd still have a season.

13:30.920 --> 13:32.670
You're the reason that
we had to forfeit that game.

13:32.670 --> 13:34.500
I didn't start
the stupid thing!

13:34.500 --> 13:35.920
Okay, okay,
knock it off.
Oh, so you're saying I did?

13:35.920 --> 13:36.670
-Back off, man!
-Knock it off!

13:36.670 --> 13:38.580
Whoa!

13:38.580 --> 13:39.830
Aah!

13:39.830 --> 13:41.290
Aah. Damn it!

13:41.290 --> 13:42.830
Just stay down there
for a second.

13:42.830 --> 13:44.040
Aah!

13:44.040 --> 13:45.460
[ Groans ]

13:45.460 --> 13:46.830
What kind of doctor
are you?

13:46.830 --> 13:48.710
Military doctor,
and this is my ER.

13:48.710 --> 13:50.670
You guys seem to think that
our rules don't apply to you,

13:50.670 --> 13:52.210
and it's cost me
two good surgeons today,

13:52.210 --> 13:54.250
so if one of you
so much as makes a sound

13:54.250 --> 13:56.380
before you're discharged
from my ER,

13:56.380 --> 13:59.210
I will send you out of here
on a stretcher. Understood?

13:59.210 --> 14:00.330
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

14:00.330 --> 14:02.580
-Okay.
-Yes, sir.
-Sorry.

14:02.580 --> 14:06.620
Oh. I like a man
with authority.

14:06.620 --> 14:08.170
Me too.

14:08.170 --> 14:09.290
[ Telephone rings ]

14:09.290 --> 14:10.920
Ohh.

14:10.920 --> 14:12.040
Aah!

14:12.040 --> 14:15.210
God, my leg! Ow!

14:15.210 --> 14:17.580
Oh, it hurts! It hurts!
[ Breathing shakily ]

14:17.580 --> 14:19.620
There's no pulse.
[ Groaning ]

14:19.620 --> 14:21.000
[ Breathing quickly ]

14:21.000 --> 14:23.420
[ Groaning continues ]

14:23.420 --> 14:24.580
Okay, it's
compartment syndrome.

14:24.580 --> 14:26.170
I'm gonna need Betadine
and a scalpel.

14:26.170 --> 14:27.750
A scalpel?!
What are you gonna do?!

14:27.750 --> 14:29.960
I need to release pressure,
or you're gonna lose your leg.

14:29.960 --> 14:31.710
[ Gasps ]
So close your eyes, okay?

14:31.710 --> 14:33.380
Yes, sir.

14:33.380 --> 14:35.210
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

14:35.210 --> 14:39.290
[ Flesh rending ]
[ Screaming ]

14:39.290 --> 14:40.750
[ Screaming, crying ]

14:40.750 --> 14:43.080
-Ohh. Wow, dude.
-Nasty!

14:43.080 --> 14:44.830
[ Screaming continues ]

14:44.830 --> 14:46.420
I said close your eyes!

14:46.420 --> 14:48.880
Don't you ever do
what you're told?!

14:48.880 --> 14:51.830
[ Monitor beeping ]

14:51.830 --> 14:52.830
[ Indistinct conversations ]

14:52.830 --> 14:54.080
Oh, that's him.

14:54.080 --> 14:55.920
Oh, the father of the girl
who lost her ear?

14:55.920 --> 14:58.250
She did not lose an ear.
We're putting it back on.

14:58.250 --> 15:00.210
Look, legal wanted someone
who witnessed the accident

15:00.210 --> 15:01.960
to be with me
when I spoke to him,

15:01.960 --> 15:03.880
so no more
"losing the ear" talk.

15:03.880 --> 15:04.710
Uh, Mr. Maurer?

15:04.710 --> 15:06.040
Finally.

15:06.040 --> 15:07.580
Thank you so much
for your patience.

15:07.580 --> 15:09.250
I'm Chief Miranda Bailey.

15:09.250 --> 15:11.750
This is Dr. Richard Webber.
I want to see
my daughter. Now.

15:11.750 --> 15:13.920
Absolutely.

15:13.920 --> 15:16.000
Let me just explain
what happened.
Mm-hmm.

15:16.000 --> 15:17.290
Oh, I've heard.

15:17.290 --> 15:18.710
She got a bad bruise
at a rugby game,

15:18.710 --> 15:21.250
and some incompetent ER doctor
cut her damn ear off.

15:21.250 --> 15:23.250
I want to
talk to my daughter.

15:23.250 --> 15:25.250
I'm afraid
she's already in surgery.

15:25.250 --> 15:26.670
She's in surgery?

15:26.670 --> 15:29.250
Are you aware Sarah has
a ventricular septal defect

15:29.250 --> 15:30.420
which can cause her
complications

15:30.420 --> 15:31.710
under
general anesthesia?

15:31.710 --> 15:34.330
Yes, we are aware,
and she's being supervised

15:34.330 --> 15:35.830
by our chief of cardio.

15:35.830 --> 15:37.170
Uh, are you a doctor?

15:37.170 --> 15:40.460
No.
Malpractice attorney.

15:40.460 --> 15:42.790
[ Chuckles ]

15:42.790 --> 15:47.080
♪♪

15:47.080 --> 15:49.460
Cardiac status
is rock steady.

15:49.460 --> 15:50.960
Wouldn't even know
she had a defect.

15:50.960 --> 15:52.620
Excellent.
Mm.

15:52.620 --> 15:54.830
So, um,
game night, huh?

15:54.830 --> 15:55.830
Oh, yeah, yeah.

15:55.830 --> 15:57.290
Amelia told you?

15:57.290 --> 15:58.830
Yeah,
should she not have?

15:58.830 --> 16:00.210
Oh, no, no.
No, you're w--

16:00.210 --> 16:02.540
You're invited, of course.

16:02.540 --> 16:06.080
Clive will be there, so you're
welcome to bring someone.

16:06.080 --> 16:08.540
Cool, yeah.
Thanks.

16:08.540 --> 16:11.540
So...are you gonna
bring someone?

16:11.540 --> 16:14.500
Yeah, I guess I'll, uh --
Yeah, I'm bringing Priya.

16:14.500 --> 16:17.080
Oh. Didn't realize you were
still seeing each other.

16:17.080 --> 16:18.960
Uh, yeah,
a couple more dates.

16:18.960 --> 16:21.420
A little bit difficult
to juggle. She travels a lot.

16:21.420 --> 16:23.540
She was in the Netherlands
last week.

16:23.540 --> 16:25.120
Oh. Vacation?

16:25.120 --> 16:27.120
Uh, no, work.
The Hague.

16:27.120 --> 16:29.040
Right.
[ Laughs ] Oh, wow.

16:29.040 --> 16:31.290
Wow, just a --
a human-rights lawyer.

16:31.290 --> 16:36.330
♪♪

16:36.330 --> 16:38.460
Clive's a stockbroker.

16:38.460 --> 16:39.710
It's nice
to date someone

16:39.710 --> 16:41.500
outside of the hospital,
isn't it?

16:41.500 --> 16:43.670
It is refreshing,
actually, yeah.
Yeah. [ Chuckles ]

16:43.670 --> 16:45.380
Talk to somebody
about something other than

16:45.380 --> 16:46.830
the latest issue
of The Lancet, so that's --

16:46.830 --> 16:48.580
[ Laughing ] Yeah.

16:48.580 --> 16:50.250
Yeah.

16:50.250 --> 16:51.750
Did you read
that article

16:51.750 --> 16:53.330
about pre-hospital
antibiotics and --

16:53.330 --> 16:55.040
That was amazing.
You read that?
Yeah.

16:55.040 --> 16:57.580
Yes, groundbreaking.
Incredible.

16:57.580 --> 16:58.710
♪♪

17:03.290 --> 17:07.290
Do you need me to go over it
with you one more time?

17:07.290 --> 17:10.620
No, no.
I understand completely.

17:11.830 --> 17:15.290
It's just...

17:15.290 --> 17:18.290
I want so badly
to support you.

17:18.290 --> 17:19.710
The people
who are courting me

17:19.710 --> 17:21.960
are corporations with money
and none of the art.

17:21.960 --> 17:24.170
I was even willing
to sell to you for less,

17:24.170 --> 17:26.330
but at this point,
your proposal, it's brilliant,

17:26.330 --> 17:28.620
but it's just theory
and dreams.

17:28.620 --> 17:30.210
Oh, it'll work.
I know it'll work.

17:30.210 --> 17:33.290
You can't know.
Not yet.

17:33.290 --> 17:34.540
And I can't sell you
my father's patent

17:34.540 --> 17:36.620
just because
you're my Mer-Mer.

17:36.620 --> 17:37.920
S-She's not.

17:37.920 --> 17:40.170
I'm sorry?

17:40.170 --> 17:41.920
She's not
your Mer-Mer anymore.

17:41.920 --> 17:45.000
She's Harper Avery-winning
surgeon Meredith Grey.

17:45.000 --> 17:46.540
With all due respect,
Dr. Cerone,

17:46.540 --> 17:48.580
please don't make the mistake
of underestimating her

17:48.580 --> 17:50.250
just because you knew her
when she was a child.

17:51.880 --> 17:54.790
I'm sorry
to disappoint you.

17:54.790 --> 17:57.960
It's the last thing
I wanted to do.

17:57.960 --> 17:59.500
Helm, get the mouse.

17:59.500 --> 18:01.000
Yes!

18:01.000 --> 18:02.540
Sorry.

18:02.540 --> 18:08.540
♪♪

18:08.540 --> 18:14.580
[ Telephone ringing,
indistinct conversations ]

18:14.580 --> 18:16.620
What's this about you not
putting in the feeding tube?

18:16.620 --> 18:17.880
Well, we might not
have to.

18:17.880 --> 18:19.080
I went
and got the signatures.

18:19.080 --> 18:20.960
I just need yours,
and we can move forward.

18:20.960 --> 18:22.250
Move forward with what?

18:22.250 --> 18:24.460
The medical marijuana.

18:24.460 --> 18:25.880
E-Excuse me?

18:25.880 --> 18:27.380
I'm authorizing marijuana
for Kimmie.

18:27.380 --> 18:28.830
She said it was your idea.

18:28.830 --> 18:32.460
To give a 12-year-old marijuana?
Are you out of your mind?!

18:32.460 --> 18:34.080
To relieve her nausea
and to keep her

18:34.080 --> 18:35.790
from needing to be
on a -- a feeding tube.

18:35.790 --> 18:37.210
She's a child.

18:37.210 --> 18:38.080
There's research
that say it's a --

18:38.080 --> 18:41.330
No! I don't care
what it says.

18:41.330 --> 18:42.830
You're not gonna turn her
into a drug addict

18:42.830 --> 18:44.210
like her parents.

18:44.210 --> 18:45.330
You're fired.

18:45.330 --> 18:47.670
I'm what?
You're fired!

18:47.670 --> 18:49.620
You're off Kimmie's case.

18:49.620 --> 18:53.420
I'm finding another doctor
at another hospital.

18:53.420 --> 18:54.920
[ Door opens ]

18:54.920 --> 18:56.120
[ Door creaks lightly ]

18:56.120 --> 18:57.620
[ Door slams ]

18:57.620 --> 18:58.920
♪♪

19:05.330 --> 19:06.620
Wh-- Am I gonna die?

19:06.620 --> 19:08.420
Yes. Probably not today,
but, yes.

19:08.420 --> 19:09.750
Dude!

19:09.750 --> 19:11.000
There was
a buildup of blood

19:11.000 --> 19:12.500
between the layers of tissue
and your leg.

19:12.500 --> 19:13.790
But i-is that fatal?

19:13.790 --> 19:15.330
Well, it could've caused you
to lose the leg.

19:15.330 --> 19:17.040
But I got it in time.

19:17.040 --> 19:18.210
Now we just need to
make sure

19:18.210 --> 19:19.920
that it doesn't
continue to bleed.

19:19.920 --> 19:22.210
It's just that, um,
there's a lot of blood,

19:22.210 --> 19:23.920
and -- and I have a term paper
I haven't finished,

19:23.920 --> 19:25.830
and -- and I have a present
for my girlfriend,

19:25.830 --> 19:27.120
and, like --
like, you know,

19:27.120 --> 19:29.040
it's j-just a sweatshirt
s-she likes,

19:29.040 --> 19:30.290
and, like...

19:30.290 --> 19:31.830
My parents!
[ Breathes shakily ]

19:31.830 --> 19:34.210
[ Voice breaking ] I never,
like, thanked them for, like --

19:34.210 --> 19:36.540
like, being my parents, and,
like, I almost died, you know?

19:36.540 --> 19:39.380
Like, what --
Okay, Chris, I need you to shut
up so I can keep saving you.

19:39.380 --> 19:42.500
Okay. Oh, I'm --
I'm sorry I threw that ball.

19:42.500 --> 19:44.710
We're good.
[ Muffled ] Okay.

19:46.420 --> 19:49.580
Patient number 66055.
38 years old.

19:49.580 --> 19:52.080
Emergency C-section
due to cord prolapse.

19:52.080 --> 19:53.540
Hmm.

19:53.540 --> 19:54.670
Questo è strano.

19:54.670 --> 19:55.670
English, please.

19:55.670 --> 19:57.880
English somewhere else,
please.

19:57.880 --> 19:59.960
Oh, your sister's
worried about you, Andrew.

19:59.960 --> 20:02.790
It -- Well, it's a headache
made worse by noise.

20:02.790 --> 20:03.960
[ Sighs ]
Sorry.

20:03.960 --> 20:05.380
Ugh.

20:05.380 --> 20:08.620
[ Quietly ] Um, I said,
"This is strange." Look.

20:08.620 --> 20:11.830
That's our hospital's, uh,
C-section rates?
Uh-huh.

20:11.830 --> 20:13.830
It was steady
until three years ago,

20:13.830 --> 20:18.420
when it started trending up,
and...look which doctor

20:18.420 --> 20:21.080
does way more of them
than the hospital average.

20:21.080 --> 20:24.790
Huh.
We should say something.

20:24.790 --> 20:26.170
O-Or maybe you could
just mention it

20:26.170 --> 20:27.790
during Lindsay
and Sofia's playdate.

20:27.790 --> 20:29.420
Oh, no, that's not what
we're studying.

20:29.420 --> 20:31.170
Besides, C-sections
don't kill moms.

20:31.170 --> 20:32.540
But they are
major surgeries,

20:32.540 --> 20:35.080
therefore more dangerous
than vaginal birth.

20:35.080 --> 20:36.540
We should only perform them

20:36.540 --> 20:38.460
when the benefits outweigh
other risk factors, just --

20:38.460 --> 20:41.460
Can we just -- Can we focus
on the bigger picture?

20:41.460 --> 20:44.500
Fine.

20:44.500 --> 20:49.290
[ Speaking Italian ]

20:49.290 --> 20:51.080
Ah. That's sexy.
What does that mean?

20:51.080 --> 20:55.040
I'll tell you
if you leave.

20:55.040 --> 20:57.830
Now, I know
it looks rough now,

20:57.830 --> 21:01.250
but...once
the swelling goes down,

21:01.250 --> 21:03.500
it'll -- it's gonna be
hardly noticeable.

21:03.500 --> 21:06.250
It'd be a lot less noticeable
if it'd stayed where it belongs.

21:06.250 --> 21:08.880
Uh, no, that surgery
went very well.

21:08.880 --> 21:10.790
When can we schedule
my next surgery?
[ Cellphone camera clicks ]

21:10.790 --> 21:12.000
Your next surgery?

21:12.000 --> 21:14.670
Dr. Pierce said
she could fix my VSD.

21:14.670 --> 21:16.750
No doctor
in this hospital

21:16.750 --> 21:18.750
is gonna lay a hand
on you again.

21:18.750 --> 21:20.170
And with the money
we're gonna sue them for --

21:20.170 --> 21:22.750
Dad.
We're not suing anybody.

21:22.750 --> 21:24.710
I don't want to be
on the sidelines anymore.

21:24.710 --> 21:26.040
I want to play.

21:26.040 --> 21:28.830
If I'm gonna get hurt, I'd
rather get hurt on the field.

21:28.830 --> 21:31.000
Can't you just cheer me on?

21:31.000 --> 21:33.000
Please?

21:33.000 --> 21:35.620
♪♪

21:35.620 --> 21:36.670
What do you mean
they're leaving?

21:36.670 --> 21:37.670
Where is she taking her?

21:37.670 --> 21:39.620
I don't know.
We need to stop it.

21:39.620 --> 21:40.830
I'll talk to Grandma Peg.

21:40.830 --> 21:41.960
No. No, you won't.
No, you won't.

21:41.960 --> 21:44.290
CBD oil is not gonna
make Kimmie an addict.

21:44.290 --> 21:45.790
Addiction is what makes
people addicts.

21:45.790 --> 21:47.000
Can you talk to her?

21:47.000 --> 21:48.170
[ Sighs ] No, Alex,
I don't disclose

21:48.170 --> 21:49.790
my personal history
to patients.

21:49.790 --> 21:51.210
Because people hear
the word "addict," and they --

21:51.210 --> 21:53.000
they make
a lot of assumptions.

21:53.000 --> 21:55.290
You're an addict?
Like that.

21:55.290 --> 21:56.880
She likes you.
She trusts you.

21:56.880 --> 21:59.000
Just talk to her.

21:59.000 --> 22:01.500
[ Telephone rings in distance ]

22:01.500 --> 22:03.120
Wow.

22:04.420 --> 22:05.420
What?

22:05.420 --> 22:07.080
Well, you've been through
the darkness.

22:07.080 --> 22:09.460
That's...sexy.

22:09.460 --> 22:10.960
[ Clears throat ]

22:10.960 --> 22:12.420
Should we check on Andrew?

22:12.420 --> 22:14.250
What if the CT missed
a tiny epidural hematoma

22:14.250 --> 22:15.670
and this is
his lucid interval

22:15.670 --> 22:17.500
and it's just in there
growing and growing,

